text: Strathisla Mills railway station served the town of Keith, Moray, Scotland from 1985 to 1993 on the Keith and Dufftown Railway. == History == The station opened in 1985 by ScotRail. It was only intended to serve visitors at Strathisla distillery. The station closed in 1993. == References == == External links == Category:Disused railway stations in Moray Category:Railway stations in Great Britain opened in 1985 Category:Railway stations in Great Britain closed in 1993 Category:1985 establishments in Scotland Category:1993 disestablishments in Scotland
